<title>SOUTH AFRICA: S.Africa's Afribrand says to seek JSE listing.</title>
<headline>S.Africa's Afribrand says to seek JSE listing.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-31</dateline>
<text>
<p>South Africa's Afribrand said on Saturday it was raising some 26 million rand in capital as preparation for seeking a listing on the Johannesburg Stock Exchange's stores sector in August.</p>
<p>The company, specialising in marketing and distributing of branded consumer products into lower-end economic markets, said in a statement about 16 million rand would be raised by public subscription and the balance by private placing.</p>
<p>Details of the issue would be released in a few weeks, Afribrand said.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
